{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:06:42.078012+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 890470cbcd8b22c382d09c9d7ffd222ed613ce36)", "id": "lc_ae9e1c20-26f8-47cf-915e-49a41a92ccd5"}, {"type": "text", "text": "#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Apply all SQL files under migrations/ to the running pgdev container.\n# Order: filename glob, lexicographic.\nset -euo pipefail\n\nCONTAINER=\"${PGDEV_CONTAINER:-pgdev_db}\"\nDB_USER=\"${POSTGRES_USER:-app}\"\nDB_NAME=\"${POSTGRES_DB:-app}\"\n\n# Note: relies on shell glob expansion ordering, not on `find`.\n# Tested on bash and zsh with default LC_COLLATE.\nfor f in migrations/*.sql; do\n    echo \"Applying $f\"\n    docker exec -i \"$CONTAINER\" psql -U \"$DB_USER\" -d \"$DB_NAME\" < \"$f\"\ndone\n", "id": "lc_60ae05da-91ee-45f6-862f-da7c40564fb4"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "21a27945-652f-46e5-b444-a196a4da4849", "tool_call_id": "call_dc65154b13df49ba81022502", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T23:06:52.848241+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## Database Migrations Walkthrough\n\nThis repository uses a **plain SQL migration** approach. The migrations live under `migrations/` and are applied in **lexicographic (alphabetical) order** by filename, using the `NNN_description.sql` convention starting at `001`.\n\nThere are currently **three migration files**, applied in this order:\n\n---\n\n### 1. `001_create_users.sql` — Create the `users` table\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE users (\n    id           BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n    email        TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,\n    display_name TEXT,\n    created_at   TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n);\n```\n\n**What it does:** Creates the foundational `users` table with:\n- `id` — auto-incrementing bigint primary key\n- `email` — unique, non-null text (the natural key)\n- `display_name` — optional display name\n- `created_at` — timestamp with time zone, defaults to the current time\n\n---\n\n### 2. `002_create_sessions.sql` — Create the `sessions` table\n\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE sessions (\n    id          UUID PRIMARY KEY,\n    user_id     BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,\n    issued_at   TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n    expires_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL\n);\n```\n\n**What it does:** Creates a session-tracking table with:\n- `id` — a UUID primary key (good for token-based session identifiers)\n- `user_id` — a foreign key to `users(id)` with `ON DELETE CASCADE` (so deleting a user automatically cleans up their sessions)\n- `issued_at` — when the session was created, defaults to now\n- `expires_at` — when the session expires (must be explicitly set)\n\n---\n\n### 3. `003_add_session_index.sql` — Add an index on `sessions.user_id`\n\n```sql\nCREATE INDEX idx_sessions_user_id ON sessions(user_id);\n```\n\n**What it does:** Adds an index on the `user_id` column in the `sessions` table. This speeds up the most common query pattern: *\"find all sessions for a given user.\"* (Note: the FK column doesn't automatically get an index in PostgreSQL, so this is a deliberate and correct addition.)\n\n---\n\n### How They're Applied\n\nThe `scripts/apply_migrations.sh` script iterates over `migrations/*.sql` using a shell glob (which expands lexicographically) and pipes each file into `psql` inside the running `pgdev_db` Docker container. There is **no migration tracking table** — it's a simple \"run them all every time\" approach, which works because all statements are `IF NOT EXISTS`-free idempotent `CREATE` statements (though you'd want to be careful adding non-idempotent migrations later).\n\n### The Big Picture\n\nThis is a clean, minimal auth scaffold:\n- **`users`** holds identity.\n- **`sessions`** holds active login sessions tied to users.\n- The index ensures session lookups by user are fast.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 687, "prompt_tokens": 7674, "total_tokens": 8361, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 34, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 7360, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.000256928, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 6.4568e-05, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00019236}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780873602-k19MiYfEXkbTa3DPQxh9", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea456-a41e-78c0-8305-5af34254bddb-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 7674, "output_tokens": 687, "total_tokens": 8361, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 7360}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 34}}}}]}}